19/04/2007
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- Southeast European (SEE) countries' army chiefs agreed in Thessaloniki on Wednesday (April 18th) to enhance military co-operation among their institutions, as a means of boosting mutual trust and regional security. 
The summit represented the first gathering of its kind. 
Senior representatives of the EU and NATO were also on hand. 
The participants decided that special task forces should be formed to work out concrete forms of collaboration in different fields. 
(Naftemporiki - 19/04/07; ANA-MPA, Tanjug - 18/04/07)
